现在欧洲应该是下决心防疫的时候了3月3日，在意大利布雷西亚，医务人员在医院外搭建的帐篷中工作。
Now it is time for Europe to make up its mind about vaccination. On March 3, in Brescia, Italy, medical staff worked in tents set up outside the hospital.
图/新华在欧洲疾病预防控制中心（ECDC）公布的《COVID-19在欧盟/欧洲经济区和英国的地理分布》图上，象征新冠病毒的红色圆点醒目地打在欧洲几乎所有国家的版图上，包括隔海相望的英国、爱尔兰和冰岛。
Photo / Xinhua On the map "COVID-19 in the European Union / European Economic Area and the Geographical Distribution of Britain," published by the European Centre for Disease Control (ECDC), red dots symbolizing the new crown virus stand out on almost all European countries, including the UK, Ireland and Iceland across the sea.
随着塞浦路斯于当地时间3月9日确认该国出现首例新冠肺炎患者，欧盟27个成员国全部中招。
With Cyprus confirming its first case of pneumonia on March 9 local time, all 27 members of the European Union have signed up.
截至欧洲中部时间3月9日8时，欧盟和英国共报告新冠病毒感染病例11577例，而结合欧洲各国的最新通报，这一不断向前滚动的数字已超过1.4万，死亡人数超过520人，比3天前已经翻了一倍。
As of 0800 CET on 9 March, 11,577 new cases of Creutzfeldt-Jakob Disease had been reported in the European Union and the United Kingdom, and the roll-forward figure was more than 14,000 and the death toll was more than 520, double the figure of three days earlier.
意大利已经成为欧洲的武汉。
Italy has become the Wuhan of Europe.
截至当地时间3月9日18时，该国累计确诊新冠肺炎病例9172例，共治愈724人，死亡463人，是中国境外死亡病例最多的国家。
By 1800 hours local time on March 9, 2007, 9172 new cases of pneumonia had been diagnosed, 724 people had been cured and 463 people had died, the highest number of deaths outside China.
意大利总理孔特9日晚宣布，10日开始在全国范围内实行封城禁令，学校停课时间延长至4月3日。
Italian Prime Minister Conte announced the night of the 10-day nationwide ban on the city, school closed until April 3.
除工作、紧急情况或医疗状况外，所有居民不得随意进出城市，出入城市者须提供自述声明。
Except for work, emergencies or medical conditions, all residents are not allowed to enter or leave the city at will, and persons entering or leaving the city are required to provide self-declaration.
同时，全国暂停全部体育赛事。
At the same time, all sporting events are suspended.
3月8日下午，意大利陆军参谋长萨尔瓦多莱·法利纳发表声明称，他本人病毒核酸检测呈阳性，目前正在自己的居所内隔离。
In the afternoon of 8 March, the Italian Army Chief of Staff, Salvador Falina, issued a statement stating that he himself was HIV-positive and was currently being quarantined in his residence.
根据政府颁布的法令和有关卫生条例，他正配合调查他最近几天的活动轨迹和接触史。
In accordance with the decree issued by the Government and the relevant health regulations, he is cooperating in the investigation of his movements and contacts in recent days.
法利纳在声明中说，他将继续履行自己的职责，但需要他本人出席的工作将由另外一名将军代替。
In his statement, Mr. Farina said he would continue to carry out his duties, but that work that required his personal presence would be replaced by another general.
此前，由于疫情发展迅猛，孔特曾于3月8日凌晨宣布封锁意大利北部伦巴第大区及该国其他大区管辖的14个省。
Earlier, on 8 March, in the early hours of 8 March, Conte had declared a blockade of the Lombardy region in northern Italy and 14 provinces under the jurisdiction of other regions of the country, owing to the rapid spread of the epidemic.
这一措施引发多地至少4所监狱发生暴动，致使20名囚犯越狱，7人死亡。
This measure triggered riots in at least four prisons, resulting in the escape of 20 prisoners and the death of 7.
美国《商业内幕》报道，因为封城措施影响了囚犯家属的探视活动，以及监狱密闭空间加剧了囚犯对新冠病毒感染感的恐慌，从而引发骚乱。
US Business Insider reports that unrest has erupted as closures have affected visits by inmates' families, and closed spaces in prisons have contributed to fears of a new crown virus infection.
意大利安莎通讯社消息，米兰南部帕维亚监狱的囚犯们破坏了监狱设施，在监狱管理人员与之进行了“漫长而艰难的谈判”后，他们才被说服返回牢房。
According to the Italian news agency ANSA, inmates at Pavia prison in southern Milan destroyed prison facilities and were persuaded to return to their cells only after "long and difficult negotiations" between prison staff and them.
在意大利之外，法国、德国、西班牙的确诊数量均已破千。
Outside Italy, the number of confirmed cases has broken through in France, Germany and Spain.
法国卫生部当地时间3月9日晚通报，累计确诊新冠肺炎病例1412例，较前一天增长286例，总计死亡病例25例。
A total of 1,412 new cases of pneumonia were confirmed, 286 more than the previous day, and 25 deaths were recorded, the Health Ministry said.
此外，法国国民议会确诊数量增至6例，其中4例为议员，2例为内部工作人员。
In addition, the number of cases confirmed by the French National Assembly increased to six, of which four were parliamentarians and two were internal staff.
目前，所有确诊病例均已被隔离，法兰西岛大区卫生局协同其它地方卫生局正在调查相关人员感染路径和接触人员。
At present, all confirmed cases are isolated and the Ile-de-France Regional Health Authority, in conjunction with other local health boards, is investigating the routes of infection and the persons contacted.
当地时间3月8日晚，法国总统马克龙就新冠肺炎疫情再次召开部长级特别国防会议。
On the night of March 8, French President Marc Ronny reconvened a special national defense conference at the ministerial level to discuss the outbreak of pneumonia.
法国卫生部长韦兰表示，法国仍处在抗疫第二阶段，工作重点依然是减缓新型冠状病毒在法国本土的传播。
France is still in the second phase of the fight against the disease, and the focus remains on slowing the spread of the new coronavirus, said French Health Minister Jean-Marie Whelan.
鉴于疫情的发展，韦兰宣布法国全境禁止集体活动的人数上限从5000下调至1000，不过各省行政长官可根据当地情况，对游行、考试、公共交通等必要的社会活动灵活处理。
As the epidemic unfolded, Whelan announced a cut in the number of people banned from holding mass events across France from 5,000 to 1,000, although prefects were free to respond flexibly to local conditions and other necessary social events, such as parades, examinations and public transport.
同时，将以政令的形式进一步为远程医疗咨询提供便利，以缓解就医压力。
At the same time, telemedicine counselling will be further facilitated in the form of a decree to relieve the pressure on medical treatment.
德国疾控机构罗伯特科赫研究所通报，截至当地时间3月9日晚，德国15个州共确诊1139例，且在疫情最严重的北威州出现了2例死亡病例。
The Robert Koch Institute, the German CDC, said there were 1,139 confirmed cases in 15 German states by the night of March 9, and two deaths in the worst affected state.
西班牙卫生部长萨尔瓦多·伊拉9日表示，西班牙将关闭一些地区的所有学校、托儿所和大学至少15天，以避免新冠病毒的持续传播。
Spain will close all schools, nurseries and universities in some areas for at least 15 days to avoid the continued spread of the virus, Spanish Health Minister Salvador Illa said Wednesday.
截至当地时间9日15时，西班牙新冠肺炎患者达到1046例，死亡26例。
As of 1500 hours local time, Spain's new crown pneumonia patients reached 1046 cases, 26 deaths.
其中首都马德里最为严重，患者数量达469例，死亡16例。
Madrid was the capital, with 469 cases and 16 deaths.
英国健康与社会保障部最新统计，英国在3月8日到3月9日间，新增确诊新冠病毒感染者46人，累计确诊319例，死亡5人。
Between March 8 and March 9, 46 new cases were confirmed, with 319 confirmed cases and five deaths, the Ministry of Health and Social Security said.
“当下英国应对新冠状病毒传播所采取的‘遏制’阶段措施看来已经难以独自发挥效果，政府正在为推迟疫情暴发进行多方准备。
"The 'containment' phase of the UK's response to the new coronavirus appears unlikely to work on its own, as the government prepares for a delay in the outbreak.
”英国首相鲍里斯·约翰逊于当地时间3月9日傍晚的公开讲话中表示，如果能将病毒传播高峰期拖延到夏天，英国公共医疗服务体系（NHS）也将更有应对能力。
British Prime Minister Boris Johnson said in a public address on the evening of March 9 that the NHS would also be more responsive if the virus's peak spread could be delayed until the summer.
英国将于本周三（3.13）就新冠病毒传播举行第三次“眼镜蛇”内阁紧急会议，针对疫情暴发进行讨论。
Britain will hold its third emergency meeting of its cobra cabinet on Wednesday (3.13) to discuss the outbreak.
英国“眼镜蛇”紧急计划委员会由其内阁成员和军警情首脑组成，拥有停止议会等无上权力，专门负责处理与国家安全有关的特别重大事宜。
The Cobra emergency planning committee, composed of members of the British cabinet and the head of the military police, has all-powerful powers, including the power to stop parliament, to deal with matters of particular importance to national security.
葡萄牙总统府网站8日通报，葡总统德索萨因曾接见的学生所在学校出现新冠肺炎确诊病例，将主动接受两周隔离，取消所有原定公务活动。
Portuguese President Jose Luis Posada will voluntarily accept a two-week quarantine and cancel all scheduled official activities in the event of a confirmed case of pneumonia in his school, the Portuguese presidential palace said Wednesday.
葡萄牙8日新增9例确诊病例，累计病例数达到30例。
Portugal 8 new 9 confirmed cases, the cumulative number of cases reached 30.
另据路透社消息，瑞典中央银行副行长弗洛登新冠病毒检测结果呈阳性。
Also according to Reuters news agency, Sweden's central bank vice-president Froden new crown virus test results are positive.
截至当地时间3月9日，瑞典新增新冠病毒感染45例，累计确诊248例，尚未有死亡病例。
As of March 9, local time, 45 new cases of Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease had been reported in Sweden, with 248 cases diagnosed and no deaths reported.
世界卫生组织总部所在国瑞士的新冠感染确诊数字也在不断上升，截止至当地时间9日12时,瑞士及列支敦士登共确诊新冠肺炎病例312例,死亡2例,治愈3例。
The number of confirmed cases of new crown pneumonia in Switzerland, the headquarters of the World Health Organization, is also on the rise, with 312 cases confirmed, 2 deaths and 3 cases cured in Switzerland and Liechtenstein as of 12: 00 local time.
世卫组织总干事谭德塞在3月9日召开的新冠肺炎疫情例行发布会上表示，当前新冠肺炎在全球100多个国家地区蔓延，成为大流行病的威胁已变得非常现实，但这将是历史上第一个可以控制的大流行病，不会任由病毒摆布。
The threat of a pandemic has become very real, but it will be the first manageable pandemic in history and will not be left to the mercy of the virus, WHO Director-General Theresa Tupper said at a regular briefing on Monday.
“欧洲各国情况不同，总的来说还处于上升期，如果用‘爆发’来形容欧洲疫情，我也不反对，但发展空间多大、什么时间结束，还很难预料，前景并不乐观。
"Europe is in a different situation and is generally on an upward trend, and I would not object to a 'breakout' to describe the epidemic in Europe, but it is difficult to predict how much space and when it will end, and the outlook is not encouraging.
”流行病学专家、中华预防医学会新冠肺炎防控专家组成员姜庆五对《中国新闻周刊》说，因新冠病毒的诊断方法、诊断技术和可及性等因素，实际感染数字可能远远多于已经确诊的。
Jiang Qingv, an epidemiologist and member of the Chinese Society of Preventive Medicine's New Crown Pneumonia Prevention and Control Team, told China News Weekly that the actual number of infections may be much higher than those already diagnosed due to factors such as diagnosis methods, diagnostic techniques and accessibility.
“现在欧洲应该是下决心防疫的时候了，不论学习哪国经验，根据传染病的特点，控制传染源、切断传播途径、保护易感人群，在没有特效药和疫苗的情况下，也没有更有效的措施。
"Now is the time for Europe to make up its mind to take precautions, regardless of the country's experience, to control the source of infection, cut off transmission routes, protect vulnerable populations, and have no more effective measures in the absence of specific drugs and vaccines, depending on the characteristics of the epidemic.
”姜庆武说。
"said Jiang.
